title: Cesarean sections in selected countries 2017
summary: This is a bar chart representing Country in the x axis and Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births in the y axis.
The Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births is highest at Country Turkey and lowest at Country Israel.
The maximum Country Turkey has got 3.58 times higher Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births than the minimum Country Israel.

max_summary: This bar chart has 25 columns on the x axis representing Country, and Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births in each Country on the y axis.
The Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births is highest at Country Turkey and lowest at Country Israel.
Second maximum Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births is found at Country Korea.
There is a difference of 383.0 between the maximum Country Turkey and minimum Country Israel.
Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births at Country Turkey is 531.4 , second place is Korea at 451.9, and thirdly is Poland at 393.0.
Country Slovak Republic, and Luxembourg share the same value 296.8.
The highest value 531.4 at Turkey is almost 1.97 times larger than the average value 269.64.
The Cesarean sections per 1,000 live births is 6741.0 if we add up values of all Countrys.
